# Callboard

A webapp for professional theatre companies to manage actor attendance. Replaces physical sign-in sheets with QR code sign-in, admin controls, and offline support.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React + Vite (in `client/`) + [React Aria](https://react-aria.adobe.com)
- **Backend**: Express API (in `server/`)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM (schema in `prisma/`)
- **Package Manager**: Yarn (workspaces for client and server)

## Terminology

- **Organization** (called "Company" in the UI): The producing theatre company. Top-level multi-tenant entity. Has a `name`, `slug`, `showTitle` (display name override used in headers/printouts; falls back to `name`), and `weekStartsOn` preference. Users belong to an Organization via a membership with a role (`owner`, `admin`, or `actor`). Company name/rename/delete is managed from the Account page.
- **Show**: An individual performance — a specific `date` + `showTime` (e.g. "2026-03-15 matinee"). Belongs to an Organization. Has a unique `signInToken` for QR code sign-in, and `activeAt`/`lockedAt` timestamps to control the sign-in window. Show-level settings (show title display name, week start, calendar import, team members) are managed from the Show Settings page within the admin area.
- **Membership** (`OrganizationMembership`): Links a User to an Organization with a role. Roles are `owner` (full control including rename/delete), `admin` (manage shows and attendance), `actor` (sign in and view callboard).
- **Attendance**: Links a User to a Show with a status: `signed_in`, `absent`, `vacation`, or `personal_day`. Tracks who signed in, when, and optionally which admin marked the status.

## Features

- **QR Code Sign-In**: Actors scan a unique QR code per Organization to sign in (must be logged in)
- **Admin Controls**: Manually sign in actors, or mark as absent, vacation, or personal day
- **Calendar Import**: Import performance calendar from CSV
- **Attendance Reports**: View and print reports
- **Offline Mode**: Print attendance sheet when offline; enter manual sign-ins when back online (Dexie for IndexedDB)

## Project Structure

- `client/` - React + Vite frontend
- `server/` - Express API
- `prisma/` - Database schema and migrations

## Data Model (Prisma)

- **Organization**: `id`, `name`, `slug` (unique URL key), `showTitle` (optional display name override), `weekStartsOn` (0=Sun…6=Sat). Has many `OrganizationMembership` and `Show`.
- **OrganizationMembership**: Links `User` ↔ `Organization` with a `MembershipRole` (`owner` | `admin` | `actor`).
- **User**: `email`, `hashedPassword`, `firstName`, `lastName`. Has many memberships and attendance records.
- **Show**: `organizationId`, `date` (date only), `showTime` (string, e.g. `"19:30"` or `"matinee"`), `signInToken` (unique, used in QR URL), `activeAt`, `lockedAt`. Unique per org + date + time.
- **Attendance**: `userId`, `showId`, `status` (`signed_in` | `absent` | `vacation` | `personal_day`), `signedInAt`, `markedByUserId`. Unique per user + show.

